docs.lead_paragraph: While the bill would protect funding for programs like infant nutrition, lawmakers warned of painful cuts for others.

headline.seo: Plan That Would Spare Vital Programs Is Expected to Pass Senate
headline.main: Finance Bill, Nearing Senate Passage, Would Protect Some Favored Programs
headline.print_headline: Finance Bill, Nearing Senate Passage, Would Protect Some Favored Programs

docs.abstract: Handful of lucky programs will be spared brunt of automatic federal spending cuts following expected Senate passage of broad legislation to finance government through end of September.
docs.snippet: While the bill would protect funding for programs like infant nutrition, lawmakers warned of painful cuts for others.

byline.original: By JONATHAN WEISMAN and ANNIE LOWREY
